                "grammar": {
                    "title": "The -kan Verb Suffix",
                    "explanation": "**-kan** shows the verb takes a direct object. Can mean doing something for someone: membuka (open) â†’ **membukakan** (open for someone). Also used in imperatives: tuliskan (write down).",
                    "examples": [
